This is equivalent to saying: at most 1 observation is greater than or equal to 27.3.

Let me count the complementary event: Y₇ ≥ 27.3 means at least 2 observations are ≥ 27.3.

So: P(Y₇ < 27.3) = 1 - P(Y₇ ≥ 27.3) = 1 - P(at least 2 observations ≥ 27.3)

For each observation:
