- P(L) = 0.19
- P(N) = 0.65
- P(I) = 0.17
- P(H|I) = 0.35 (of those with irregular heartbeat, 35% have high BP)
- P(I|N) = 0.11 (of those with normal BP, 11% have irregular heartbeat)

I need to find: P(R and L) = P(R ∩ L)

